snippet.textDisplay:
After this season of the XFL, you'll really be able to feel the
difference when you are watching the NFL and they call a bogus ruling on
the field and you weren't able to hear the back conversation of how
they came to that decision. "See, in the XFL at least we would have
heard the rationale behind the call" will be what the fans are saying.
I.E. how that Bogus tripping call impacted the Dallas Cowboys vs. the
New England Patriots in Week 12. Wouldn't happen in the XFL because we can all hear the refs have to explain themselves.

snippet.textDisplay:
Now what I like ...I like the kickoffs...The kick-offs look really cool on TV... And you get a return almost every time with a potential for a touchdown and you're also protecting the players Because you're basically eliminating that head on collision of 40 miles an hour. I like the extra point rules.
So... kind of looks like not a whole lot of thought put into the uniforms... Which kind of blows me away because when you're competing with the NFL ...seems like you want to make a powerful first impression... at least with some better uniforms you can have the appearance of being a first class |"NFL level" of competition... the semi-pro football teams around here have better uniforms than these guys. also you can tell they're not real committed Ted the league I just went to their website to check on the official XFL footballs and they're sold out pretty much for all of their teams... So they were like yeah we're pretty sure it's going to be successful but yeah kind of not really we don't want to be stuck with 10,000 football's case this thing fails and I mean I can appreciate that from a business point of view they got plenty of eight-year-old boys in Sri Lanka that can probably manufacture another 10 ,000 if they needed to pretty quick

The best part of XFL is when the coach puts his playcard over his mouth so the other team can't read his lips....but then the XFL broadcasts the coaches voice so everyone can hear it, and then the XFL commentator tells everyone what play is about to happen. Like this

"Well Chuck....Zeus 99 means that the running back is about to run right and the two offensive linesman will shift to create a gap!"

Maybe it's not a good idea to blurt out to the whole world what the play is about to be 😃

The other team just might steal that information....maybe
